Add sidebar to interface to depict pending appointments
commitResults.messageBody:
The application currently does not allow the user to view upcoming appointments in an intuitive and convenient manner.

Adding a sidebar containing upcoming appointments allows users to look through what are their upcoming appointments which allows them to plan their future schedules out more easily.

Let's:
- Create a sidebar that contains upcoming appointments
- Sort the appointments in the sidebar in chronological order
- For each entry in the sidebar, they contain the appointment name, the client's name, date and time of the appointment.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add confirmation page for clear command
commitResults.messageBody:
The clear command is not protected by any validation. This
makes new users vulnerable to deleting their contact book while learning
how to use it.

Adding a confirmation page allows users to stop and think about the
ramifications of their actions and reduces the likelihood of mistakes
that can worsen the user experience.

Let's add a confirmation page.

commitResults.messageTitle: Modify Find Command to accept financial plans and tags
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, the find command is rather limited in scope. It is only able
to search for names while a user might want to search by financial plans
or tags.

Let's:
- Expand the find command to search by tags and financial plans
  (substrings included)

We choose to search names by whole words because it is unlikely to
search for names by substrings, while tags and financial plans may have
substrings that make sense to search for.

Testing will be added in a future commit.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add CombinedPredicate class and tests for previous commit
commitResults.messageBody:
The current predicate implementation makes it difficult to determine
if two predicates for a Person are the same. This implementation makes
it slightly easier to compare, such that as long as the keywords within
each component predicate are ordered in a certain way, then two
CombinedPredicates will be the same. It's good enough for the current
purpose anyway.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add changes to userguide for sortcommand
Update sort command to include sort by appointment timing functionality.
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, the sort command can only sort by person name in lexicographical order.
This new implementation enables users to additionally sort by appointment date and time
with the earlier appointment being displayed first.

The sort command in the CLI has also been altered. Instead of the usual sort just
sorting by lexicographical order, this has now been changes to "sort sort" to make
"sort" a default "help function" and "sort appointment" to be sorting by the appointment
time.

Currently, when scheduling an appointment with a person with an appointment
scheduled, the schedule command overrides the old appointment without
the users knowledge.

This fix keeps the implementation of this overriding appointment but adds a
prompt that lets users know the current appointment scheduled and asks the
user if he would like to override the appointment

This is done to enable schedule to have dual functionality of adding and
editting as well as a reminder of a potentially forgotten appointment with
a person and also as a quick way to override past appointments with a new
one.
